text=THE  BEGINNING %0a%0aOF %0a%0aTHE    FIRST   BOOK %0a%0aOP %0a%0aTHEOPHILUS    THE    MONK, %0a%0aUPON    VARIOUS    ARTS. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTER  I. %0a%0aOF  THB  MIXTURE  OF   COLOURS   FOR  THE   NUDE. %0a%0aThe  colour  which  is  called  flesh  colour,  with  which  the  face %0aand  the  nude  are  painted,  is  thus  composed.  Take  ceruse, %0athat  is  white  which  is  made  from  lead,  and  put  it,  not  ground, %0abut  dry  as  it  is,  into  a  copper  or  iron  vessel,  and  place  it  upon %0aglowing  coals,  and  bum  it  until  it  is  concerted  into  a  yellow %0acolour.  Then  grind  it,  and  mix  with  it  white  ceruse,  and %0acinnabar,  until  it  is  made  like  flesh.  The  mixture  of  these %0acolours  may  be  made  according  to  your  will ;  so  that  if  you %0awish  to  have  red  coloured  faces,  add  more  cinnabar ;  but  if %0aclear  complexions,  put  more  white;  if  pallid  however,  add, %0afor  cinnabar,  a  little  green. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTER  II. %0a%0aOF  THE   COLOUR  CALLED   PRA8INU8. %0a%0aWhich  prasinus  is  a  preparation  having  the  appearance  of  a %0agreen  colour  with  black ;  such  is  the  nature  of  which,  that  it  is %0anot  ground  upon  the  stone,  but,  placed  in  water  it  is  dis- %0asolved, and  is  carefully  strained  through  a  cloth ;  its  use  is %0arather  advantageous  upon  a  new  wall  for  a  green  colour. %0a%0aB  2 %0a%0a%0a4  THEOPHILI    LIBER    I. %0a%0aCAPUT   III. %0a%0aDE    P08C   PRIMO. %0a%0aCUM  vero  membrinam  miscueris  inde  facies  et  nuda  cor- %0apora impleveris,  admisce  ei  prasinum  et  rubeum,  qui %0acomburitur  ex  ogra,  et  modicum  cenobrii,  et  confice  pose,  ex %0aquo  desiguabis  supercilia  et  oculos,  nares,  et  os,  mentuni,  et %0afossulas  circa  nares,  et  tempora,  rugas  in  fronte  et  collo,  et %0arotunditatem  faciei,  barbas  juvenum  et  articulos  manuum  et %0apedum,  et  omnia  membra,  quae  distinguuntur  in  nudo  corpore. %0a%0a%0aCAPUT   IV. %0a%0aDE    ROSA    PRIMA. %0a%0a%0aDEINDE  misce  cum  simplici  membrina  modicum  cenobrii %0aet  parum  minii,  et  confice  colorem,  qui  dicitur  rosa,  unde %0arubricabis  maxillam  utramque,  os  et  mentum  inferins,  coUum %0aet  rugas  frontis  modice,  ipsam  frontem  super  tempora  ex %0autraque  parte,  nasum  in  longitudine  et  supemares  ex  utraque %0aparte,  articulos  et  csetera  membra  in  nudo  corpore. %0a%0a%0aCAPUT    V. %0a%0aOE   LUMINA   PRIMA. %0a%0a%0aPOST  heec  misce  cum  simplici  membrina  cerosam  tritam, %0aet  compone  colorem,  qui  dicitur  lumina,  unde  illuminabis %0asupercilia,  nasum  in  longitudine  et  super  foramina  narium  ex %0autraque  parte,  subtiles  tractus  circa  oculos  et  tempora  inferius, %0aet  mentum  superius,  juxta  nares  et  os  ex  utraque  parte,  fron- %0atem superius,  inter  rugas  frontis  modice,  et  collum  in  medio, %0aet  circa  aures,  ac  articulos  manuum  et  pedum  exterius  et %0aomnem  rotunditatem  manuum,  pedum  et  brachiorum  in  medio. %0a%0a%0aTRANSLATION.  5 %0a%0aCHAPTER  III, %0a%0aOF   THE   FIRST   P08C,    OR    HALF   SHADOW. %0a%0aWhen  you  have  mixed  the  flesh  colour,  and  have  filled  in  the %0afaces  and  the  nude  with  it,  raix  with  it  some  deep  green  and %0athe  red  which  is  burnt  from  ochre,  and  a  little  cinnabar ;  and %0aprepare  the  half  shadow,  with  which  you  will  mark  the  eye- %0abrows and  eyes,  the  nostrils  and  mouth,  the  chin  and  the %0ahollows  round  the  nostrils,  and  the  temples ;  the  wrinkles  in %0athe  forehead  and  neck,  and  the  rounding  of  the  face ;  the %0abeards  of  young  men,  and  the  articulations  of  the  hands  and %0afeet,  and  all  members  which  are  made  apparent  in  the  nude. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTEB.  IV. %0a%0aOP   THE   FIRST   ROSE   COLOUR. %0a%0a%0aThen  mix  with  the  simple  flesh  colour  a  little  cinnabar  and  a %0alittle  minium,  and  prepare  the  colour  which  is  called  rose, %0awith  which  you  will  redden  both  cheeks,  the  mouth  and  lower %0apart  of  the  chin,  the  neck,  and  wrinkles  of  the  forehead %0aslightly,  the  forehead  itself  above  the  temples  on  either  side, %0athe  nose  in  its  length  and  over  the  nostrils  on  eitlier  side,  the %0aarticulations  and  other  members  in  the  nude. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTER  V. %0a%0aOP   THE   FIRST    RELIEF. %0a%0a%0aAfter  this  mix,  with  simple  flesh  colour,  ceruse,  ground,  and %0acompose  a  colour  which  is  called  relief,  with  which  you  will %0alighten  the  eyebrows,  the  nose  in  its  length,  and  above  the %0aopenings  of  the  nostrils  on  either  side,  fine  lines  around  the %0aeyes,  the  lower  part  of  the  temples  and  upper  part  of  the  chin, %0aabout  the  nostrils  and  the  mouth  on  either  side,  the  upper %0apart  of  the  forehead,  slightly  between  the  wrinkles  of  the %0aforehead,  and  in  the  middle  of  the  neck  and  round  the  ears, %0aalso  the  articulations  of  the  hands  and  feet  outside,  and  all %0aroundness  in  the  centre  of  the  hands,  feet  and  arms. %0a%0a%0aO  THBOPHILl    LIBER    I. %0a%0aCAPUT    VI. %0a%0aDB  VBNEOA  IN  OCULIS  PONBNOA. %0a%0aDEINDE  commisce  nigrum  cum  medico  albo,  qui  color %0aYocatur  veneda,  et  imple  pupillas  oculorum.  Adde  ei %0aetiam  de  albo  ampliusy  et  imple  ocuIob  ex  utraque  parte,  et %0aalbum  simplex  linies  inter  pupillam  et  ipsum  colorem,  et  cum %0aaqua  lavabis. %0a%0a%0aCAPUT    VII. %0a%0aDE   POSC   SBOUNDO. %0a%0a%0aPOSTEA  accipe  pose,  de  quo  supra  dictum  est,  et  ad- %0amisce  ei  amplius  de  prasino  et  rubeo,  ita  ut  umbra  sit %0aanterioris  coloris,  et  imple  medium  spatium  inter  supercilia  et %0aoculos,  et  sub  oculis  medium,  et  juxta  nasum,  et  inter  os  et %0amentum,  granos  seu  barbulas  adolescentum,  et  palmas  dimi- %0adias  versus  poUicem,  et  pedes  supra  minores  articulos,  et  facies %0apuerorum  et  mulierum  a  mento  usque  ad  tempora. %0a%0a%0aCAPUT    VIII. %0a%0aDB   ROSA   BECUNDA. %0a%0aDEINDE  misce  cum  rosa  cenobrium,  et  linies  inde  in %0amedio  oris,  ita  ut  anterior  superius  inferiusque  pareat, %0aet  fac  subtiles  tractus  super  rosam  in  facie,  in  coUo  et  in  fronte, %0aet  designabis  inde  articulos  in  palmis,  et  Juncturas  omnium %0amembrorum  et  ungula. %0a%0a%0aTRANSLATION.  7 %0a%0aCHAPTER  VI. %0a%0aOF  THE  VENBDA  FOR  PLACING  UPON  THE  EYES. %0a%0aThen  mix  black  with  a  little  white,  which  colour  is  called %0aveneda,  and  fill  up  the  pupils  of  the  eyes.  Add  to  it  yet %0amore  white,  and  fill  in  the  eyes  on  both  sides,  and  lay  white %0aonly  between  the  pupil  and  this  colour,  and  you  will  wash  it %0awith  water. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTER  VII. %0a%0aOF  THE   SECOND   POSC,   OR  SHADOW   COLOUR. %0a%0aAfterwards  take  the  pose,  which  has  been  mentioned  before, %0aand  mix  with  it  more  prasinus  and  red,  so  that  it  may  become %0aa  shadow  to  the  former  colour,  and  fill  up  the  middle  space %0abetween  the  eyebrow  and  the  eyes,  and  in  the  middle  under %0athe  eyes,  and  about  the  nose,  and  between  the  mouth  and  the %0achin,  the  down  or  slight  beards  of  youths,  and  the  half-palms %0atowards  the  thumb,  and  the  feet  over  the  smaller  articulations, %0aand  faces  of  boys  and  women,  from  the  chin  to  the  temples. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTER  VIIL %0a%0aOF  THE   SECOND   ROSE   COLOUR. %0a%0aThen  mix  cinnabar  with  rose  colour,  and  paint  with  it  in  the %0amiddle  of  the  mouth,  so  that  the  former  colour  may  appear %0aabove  and  below  it ;  and  make  fine  touches  upon  the  rose %0acolour  in  the  face,  in  the  neck,  and  on  the  forehead,  and  mark %0athe  articulations  with  it  in  the  palms,  and  the  joints  of  all  the %0amembers,  and  the  nails. %0a%0a%0a8  THEOPHILI    LIBER    I. %0a%0aCAPUT    IX. %0a%0aDE   LUHINA   SECUNOA. %0a%0aET  si  facies  tenebrosa  fuerit  ut  ei  non  sufficiat  una  lumina, %0aadde  ei  amplius  de  albo  et  super  priorem  linies  subtiles %0atractus  per  omnia. %0a%0a%0aCAPUT    X. %0a%0a0£   CAPILLIS   PUERORUMy   ADOLESCENTUM    BT  JUVENUM. %0a%0aPOST  hsec  misce  modicum  nigrum  cum  ogra  et  imple %0acapillos  puerorum,  et  disceme  eos  cum  nigro.  Adde %0aamplius  nigri  cum  ogra  et  imple  capillos  adolescentum^  et %0aillumina  cum  prima.  Adde  amplius  adhuc  nigri  et  imple  ca- %0apillos juvenum,  et  illumina  cum  secundo. %0a%0a%0aCAPUT    XL %0a%0aDE    BARBIS   ADOLESCENTUM. %0a%0a%0aMISCE  prasin  et  rubeum  et  si  vis  rosse  modicum,  et %0aimple  barbas  adolescentum.  Misce  ogram  et  nigrum %0aet  rubeum,  et  imple  capillos  et  illumina  ogra  modico  nigro %0amixta,  et  ex  eadem  mixtura  fac  nigros  tractus  in  barba. %0a%0a%0aCAPUT    XII. %0a%0aDE  CAPILLIS   ET   BARBA  DECREPITORUM  ET   SENUM. %0a%0aMISCE  modicum  nigri  cum  cerosa,  et  imple  capillos  et %0abarbas  decrepitorum.  Adde  eidem  colori  amplius  nigri %0aet  modicum  rubei,  et  fac  inde  tractus,  et  illuminabis  simplici %0acerosa.     Commisce  rursum  cerosee  amplius  nigri,  et  imple  ca- %0a%0a%0aTRANSLATION.  9 %0a%0aCHAPTER  IX. %0a%0aOF   THE    SECOND    RELIEF. %0a%0aAnd  if  a  face  be  dark  so  that  one  relief  does  not  suffice  for  it, %0aadd  more  white  to  it,  and  paint  fine  touches  over  the  first %0aeverywhere. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTER  X. %0a%0aOF  THE  HAIR  OF  BOYS,  YOUTHS,  AND  YOUNG  MEN. %0a%0aAfter  this,  mix  a  little  black  with  ochre,  and  fill  in  the  hair %0aof  boys,  and  mark  them  out  with  black.  Add  more  black %0awith  ochre,  and  fill  in  the  hair  of  youths,  and  lighten  with  the %0afirst.  Add  yet  more  black,  and  fill  in  the  hair  of  young  men, %0aand  lighten  it  with  the  second. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTER  XI. %0a%0aOF   THE   BEARDS   OF   YOUTHS. %0a%0a%0aMix  deep  green  and  red,  and,  if  you  like,  a  little  rose  colour, %0aand  fill  in  the  beards  of  youths :  mix  ochre  and  black  and %0ared,  and  fill  in  the  hair,  and  lighten  with  ochre  mixed  with  a %0alittle  black,  and  from  the  same  mixture  make  the  dark  strokes %0ain  the  beard. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTER  XII. %0a%0aOF  THE  HAIR  AND  BEARDS  OF  OLD  AND  DECREPIT  MEN. %0a%0aMix  a  little  black  with  ceruse,  and  fill  in  the  hair  and  beards %0aof  decrepit  men.  Add  more  black  and  a  little  red  to  the %0asame  colour,  and  make  the  drawing  with  it,  and  lighten  simply %0awith  ceruse.     Mix  again  with  ceruse  some  more  black,  and %0a%0a%0a10  THBOPHILI    LIBBR    I. %0a%0apillos  et  barbas  senuniy  et  fac  tractatos  ex  eodem  colore,  ad- %0amixto  ei  nigro  amplius  et  medico  rubeo,  et  illumina  eo  unde %0adecrepitos  impleveras.  Eo  ordine,  si  vis,  adhuc  nigriores %0acapilloB  et  barbas  compone. %0a%0a%0aCAPUT    XIII. %0a%0aDB   BXUDRA   BT   CBTBRI8   COLORIBU8   VULTUUM. %0a%0aDEINDE  admisce  nibeo  modicum  nigri,  qui  color  dicitur %0aexudra,  et  fac  inde  tractus  circa  vultuum,  pupiOas  ocu- %0alorum,  et  in  medio  oris^et  subtiles  tractus  inter  os  et  mentum. %0aPost  heec  cum  simplici  rubeo  fac  supercilia,  et  subtiles  tractus %0ainter  oculos  et  supercilia  et  oculos  inferius,  in  plena  facie %0anasum  in  dextera  parte^,  supemares  ex  utraque  parte,  et  os %0ainferius,  et  circa  frontem  et  maxillas  senum  interius,  et  circa %0adigitos  manuum  et  articulos  pedum  interius,  et  in  conversa %0afacie  circa  nares  in  anteriori  parte.  Supercilia  vero  senum %0asire  decrepitorum  fades  cum  veneda,  unde  pupillas  implesti. %0aDeinde  cum  simplici  nigro  juvenum  supercilia  facies,  ita  ut %0asuperius  aliquantulum  rubei  appareat,  et  oculos  superius  et %0aforamina  narium,  et  os  ex  utraque  parte,  et  circa  auriculas, %0amanus  et  digitos  exterius,  et  articulos  et  cssteros  corporis %0atractus.  Omnes  rero  tractus  circa  nuda  corpora  fac  cum %0arubeo,  et  ungues  designabis  cum  exteriori  rosa. %0a%0a%0aCAPUT    XIV. %0a%0aDB  MIXTURA   VESTIMENTORUM   IN    LAQUEARI. %0a%0aMISCE  manisc  cum  folio  sive  cum  nigro,  et  modico  rubeo, %0aet  imple  vestimentum.     Admisce  etiam  modicum  nigri %0aet  fac  tractus.     Deinde  misce  lazur  cum  modico  manisc,  sive %0a%0a'  Si  ad  dcxtorain  partem  respicieiiB  pertiBcta  vel  figurata  ait  fiiclcs ;  aut  in  sinistra, %0asi  ad  sinistram  vertatur :  JSx  Cod.  Reg. %0a%0a%0aTRANSLATION.  1 1 %0a%0afill  in  the  hair  and  beards  of  old  men,  and  make  the  drawings %0afrom  the  same  colour  with  more  black  and  a  little  red  added, %0aand  lighten  it  with  that  with  which  you  filled  in  the  hair  of %0adecrepit  men.  In  this  order,  if  you  wish,  compose  hair  and %0abeards  still  darker. %0a%0a%0aCHAPTER  XIII. %0a%0aOF  EXUDRA  AND  OTHER  COLOURS  OF  COUNTENANCES. %0a%0aThen  mix  a  little  black  with  red,  which  colour  is  called %0aexudra,  and  make  drawings  with  it  round  the  faces,  the  pupils %0aof  the  eyes,  and  in  the  middle  of  the  mouth,  and  fine  touches %0abetween  the  mouth  and  the  chin.  After  this,  with  simple  red, %0amake  the  eyebrows  and  fine  lines  between  the  eyes  and  eye- %0abrows and  below  the  eyes,  the  nose  on  the  right  side  in  full %0aface,  upon  the  nostrils  on  either  side,  and  below  the  mouth, %0aand  about  the  forehead,  and  between  the  jaws  of  old  men ; %0aand  about  the  fingers  of  the  hands,  and  within  the  articula- %0ations of  the  feet,  and  about  the  nostrils  in  the  prominent  part %0ain  a  profile.  But  make  the  eyebro